  <data name="Label1.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Created By Wagnard.

Contributor : Shady7557

Thanks to anyone who put their system at risk (special thanks to Dellon132)

Whats it does is removing the Display driver from device manager
 and removing the current and all precedent driver from the windows Driver store.

Registry value are clean up correctly for NVIDIA ,for AMD there are still work to be done.

The current effect after you use this tool will be similar as if its the first time you install 
a new driver (a bit like a fresh install of windows)

WHY USE THIS TOOL:

-Maybe help pwople with problem upgrading to newer driver because of some odd 
corruption / registry error

-People who always like it clean.

-Avoid known conflict like the recent one with AMD and their OpenCL driver resulting in 
a crash with some OpenCL application. (This part has not been implemented yet)

RECOMMENDED USAGE :

- Make a RESTORE POINT (quite important) just in case...

- I personally recommend that you disconnect the internet while doing this because sometimes 
after the uninstall, windows update may be re-installing a driver on its own without authorization...

- I would like to gather feedback from you guys because its the first release so there might 
be bug and also risk so make a backup or a system restore (but it should normally be pretty safe).

-For people with driver problem, if this tool gave you any success into fixing some issue you are 
currently experiencing, please share your result.

AMD / NVIDIA have nothing to do with this application. Thanks for Microsoft for their 
wonderful tool called "devcon"</value>
